{"title_page": "National Institute of Design, Vijayawada", "text_new": "{{short description|Design school in Vijayawada, India}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=October 2018}}\n{{Infobox university\n|  name             = National Institute of Design\n|  coordinates      = {{coord|16.373354|80.526540|type:edu|display=inline,title}}\n|  established      = 2015\n|  type             = Autonomous Institution of National Importance\n|  director         = Sekhar Mukherjee\n|  city             = [[Guntur]]\n|  state            = [[Andhra Pradesh]]\n|  country          = India\n|  undergrad        = 240\n|  website          = {{url|nid.ac.in}}\n|  campus           = [[Rural area|Rural]]\n|  mascot           = \n}}\n[[File:StudioNIDV.jpg|thumb]]\n[[File:Librarynidv.jpg|thumb|Knowledge Management Centre|205x205px]]\nThe '''National Institute of Design, Andhra Pradesh''' ('''NID - AP''') is a design school in [[Vijayawada]], India. The institute started functioning on 7 September 2015.  It institute functions as an autonomous body under the Department of Industrial Policy and Promotion, Ministry of Commerce and Industry, [[Government of India]].  It is temporarily at Acharya Nagarjuna University on Guntur - Vijayawada highway (NH 16) and will move to a permanent {{convert|50|acre|adj=on}} campus\nin [[Amaravati]], the new capital city of [[Andhra Pradesh]].\n\n== Courses offered ==\nThe institute offers undergraduate diploma courses such as a diploma in Communication Design and a diploma in Textile and Apparel Design.{{citation needed|date=August 2019}}\n\n=== Graduate Diploma Program in Design (GDPD) ===\nThis 4-year course is offered in three specializations by NID Andhra Pradesh. Until 2014, [[National Institute of Design, Ahmedabad|NID Ahemdabad]] also conferred this diploma, however it has conferred a bachelor's degree since 2014 when the National Institute of Design Act 2014 was passed, allowing the institute to do so. This course has a total of 60 seats. Even though it is a Diploma level certification, it is at par with the other NIDs by virtue of it being an autonomous Institute under the Central Government.\n\n== Infrastructure ==\nThe transit campus for the institute has been set up at the EEE & ECE Block, [[Acharya Nagarjuna University]]. The current campus include Studios, Knowledge Management Centre (Library) and I.T. Lab which is par excellence. Also, the institute provides students with full-time internet access for all kinds of research and knowledge gathering.\n\n== Proposed NIDs ==\n[[National Institute of Design, Kurukshetra]] is under construction which was opened by Haryana CM Bhupendra Singh Hooda in 2012. The creation of four NIDs was suggested as part of the Government's 2007 National Design Policy.<ref name=\"toi-1-apr-2012\">[http://epaper.timesofindia.com/Default/Scripting/ArticleWin.asp?From=Archive&Source=Page&Skin=TOINEW&BaseHref=TOIA/2012/04/01&PageLabel=6&EntityId=Ar00604&ViewMode=HTML \"PPP model for new NIDs Nixed\". Times of India, Ahmedabad.  Times City section, page 6.  1 April 2012.]</ref>\n\nThe foundation stone for [[National Institute of Design, Jorhat|National Institute of Design Jorhat]] was laid by Indian Prime Minister Manmohan Singh in February 2011,<ref name=\"hindu-19-feb-2011\">[http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/article1471990.ece \"Centre committed to development of Assam, northeast: Manmohan\". The Hindu, 19 February 2011]</ref> while land has also been earmarked for the Andhra Pradesh campus in the state capital [[Amaravati (state capital)|Amaravati]].\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{National Institutes of Design}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:National Institutes of Design]]\n[[Category:Universities and colleges in Vijayawada]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Design school in Vijayawada, India}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=October 2018}}\n{{Infobox university\n|  name             = National Institute of Design\n|  coordinates      = {{coord|16.373354|80.526540|type:edu|display=inline,title}}\n|  established      = 2015\n|  type             = Autonomous Institution of National Importance\n|  director         = Sekhar Mukherjee\n|  city             = [[Guntur]]\n|  state            = [[Andhra Pradesh]]\n|  country          = India\n|  undergrad        = 240\n|  website          = {{url|nid.ac.in}}\n|  campus           = [[Rural area|Rural]]\n|  mascot           = \n}}\n[[File:StudioNIDV.jpg|thumb]]\n[[File:Librarynidv.jpg|thumb|Knowledge Management Centre|205x205px]]\nThe '''National Institute of Design, Andhra Pradesh''' ('''NID - AP''') is a design school in [[Vijayawada]], India. The institute started functioning on 7 September 2015.  It institute functions as an autonomous body under the Department of Industrial Policy and Promotion, Ministry of Commerce and Industry, [[Government of India]].  It is temporarily at Acharya Nagarjuna University on Guntur - Vijayawada highway (NH 16) and will move to a permanent {{convert|50|acre|adj=on}} campus\nin [[Amaravati]], the new capital city of [[Andhra Pradesh]].\n\n== Courses offered ==\nThe institute offers undergraduate diploma courses such as a diploma in Communication Design and a diploma in Textile and Apparel Design.{{citation needed|date=August 2019}}\n\n=== Graduate Diploma Program in Design (GDPD) ===\nThis 4-year course is offered in three specializations by NID Andhra Pradesh. Until 2014, [[National Institute of Design, Ahmedabad|NID Ahemdabad]] also conferred this diploma, however it has conferred a bachelor's degree since 2014 when the National Institute of Design Act 2014 was passed, allowing the institute to do so. This course has a total of 60 seats. Even though it is a Diploma level certification, it is at par with the other NIDs by virtue of it being an autonomous Institute under the Central Government.\n\n== Infrastructure ==\nThe transit campus for the institute has been set up at the EEE & ECE Block, [[Acharya Nagarjuna University]]. The current campus include Studios, Knowledge Management Centre (Library) and I.T. Lab which is par excellence. Also, the institute provides students with full-time internet access for all kinds of research and knowledge gathering.\n\n== Proposed NIDs ==\n[[National Institute of Design, Kurukshetra]] is under construction which was opened by Haryana CM Bhupendra Singh Hooda in 2012. The creation of four NIDs was suggested as part of the Government's 2007 National Design Policy.<ref name=\"toi-1-apr-2012\">[http://epaper.timesofindia.com/Default/Scripting/ArticleWin.asp?From=Archive&Source=Page&Skin=TOINEW&BaseHref=TOIA/2012/04/01&PageLabel=6&EntityId=Ar00604&ViewMode=HTML \"PPP model for new NIDs Nixed\". Times of India, Ahmedabad.  Times City section, page 6.  1 April 2012.]</ref>\n\nThe foundation stone for [[National Institute of Design, Jorhat|National Institute of Design Jorhat]] was laid by Indian Prime Minister Manmohan Singh in February 2011,<ref name=\"hindu-19-feb-2011\">[http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/article1471990.ece \"Centre committed to development of Assam, northeast: Manmohan\". The Hindu, 19 February 2011]</ref> while land has also been earmarked for the Andhra Pradesh campus in the state capital [[Amaravati (state capital)|Amaravati]].\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{National Institutes of Design}}\n\n[[Category:National Institutes of Design]]\n[[Category:Universities and colleges in Vijayawada]]\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences:add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/National_Institute_of_Design,_Vijayawada"}
